            .</p>
               <p>WILLIAM BRADICK. I am a <rs id="t18321018-239-viclabel1351" type="occupation">turner and bedsteadmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-239-victim2079 t18321018-239-viclabel1351"></join>; the prisoner was eighteen months in my employ -I was from home when these things were taken.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you pay me any wages on Saturday night? A. Every Saturday; I have his signature in my book up to the last fortnight that he worked for me - when I was absent my wife has overpaid him; I never knew him pawn my property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-239-person2080">
                  JAMES 
                  ALDOUS
               <interp inst="t18321018-239-person2080" type="surname" value="ALDOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-239-person2080" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-239-person2080" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, in Berwick-street. On the 7th of September the prisoner pawned a cramp, for 4s.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-239-person2081">
                  JOHN 
                  NEEDS
               <interp inst="t18321018-239-person2081" type="surname" value="NEEDS"></interp>
